      "dimensions": 1,
      "description": "nointerp - Use the value of the nearest sample. linear - Use linear interpolation between samples when the interval is lengthened. Averages all samples near the new sample when the interval is shortened. cubic - Cubically interpolates between samples, for smoother curves than Linear. This method is not recommended for channels with sharp changes. edge - A linear interpolation that recognizes single sample pulses and preserves their height and one sample width. A pulse is a non-zero value preceded and followed by zero-value samples.",
      "tooltip": "",
